You need to know these commands for the apt package manager (using tree as an example).
Operation
Command
Description
Update List
sudo apt update
Refreshes list of available software.
Install
sudo apt install tree
Installs the package 'tree'.
Operation Command Description
Remove
sudo apt remove tree
Removes package but keeps config files.
Purge
sudo apt purge tree
Removes package AND config files.
Check Install
`dpkg -l
grep tree`
Check Path
which tree
Shows where the file is located.
Clean Up
sudo apt autoremove
Deletes unused dependencies.
